<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="482" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,1481,1974]" pageId="23" pageNumber="482">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1841,1866]" pageId="23" pageNumber="482">Remarks.</emphasis>
Lowe (
<date box="[402,502,1841,1866]" pageId="23" pageNumber="482" value="1843" valueMax="1860">1843–60</date>
) gives a detailed description of this species leaving no doubt that he is referring to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Geoffroy Saint-Hilaire" baseAuthorityYear="1817" box="[151,269,1877,1902]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Myliobatidae" genus="Pteromylaeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="23" pageNumber="482" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bovinus">
<emphasis box="[151,269,1877,1902]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="482">A. bovinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and not 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[366,475,1877,1902]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Myliobatidae" genus="Myliobatis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="23" pageNumber="482" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aquila">
<emphasis box="[366,475,1877,1902]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="482">M. aquila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation box="[489,662,1877,1902]" pageId="23" pageNumber="482" refId="ref22842" refString="Gunther, A. (1870) Catalogue of the Fishes in the British Museum. Vol. 8. British Museum (Natural History), London, 549 pp." type="book">Günther (1870)</bibRefCitation>
refers at least three specimens from 
<collectingRegion box="[1074,1170,1877,1902]" country="Portugal" name="Madeira" pageId="23" pageNumber="482">Madeira</collectingRegion>
, two of them sent by R. T. Lowe. Although there are no specimens in the 
<collectionCode box="[740,805,1914,1937]" country="Portugal" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/mme0-gx6r" name="Museu Municipal do Funchal" pageId="23" pageNumber="482">MMF</collectionCode>
collections, this record was confirmed by underwater photos (
<bibRefCitation box="[240,430,1949,1974]" pageId="23" pageNumber="482" refId="ref27192" refString="Wirtz, P., Fricke, R. &amp; Biscoito, M. J. (2008) The coastal fishes of Madeira Island - new records and an annotated check-list. Zootaxa, 1715, 1 - 26." type="journal article">
Wirtz 
<emphasis box="[311,361,1949,1974]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="482">et al</emphasis>
. 2008
</bibRefCitation>
and the authors).
</paragraph>
